latestIgtvVideos.title: #ad Get The Look : The Rachel Blow Dry
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
#ad Get The Look : The Rachel Blow Dry 
So right now, we may have found ourselves with a bit more time on our hands, so I’ve teamed up with @Babyliss to show you how to create the Rachel (from Friends) blow dry using the amazing Big Hair 50mm Styler. 
I always find doing my hair and make-up makes me feel a little more normal at the moment, so thought this would be the perfect time to share this tutorial. 
The Big Hair Styler is SO easy to use and creates a salon perfect blow dry within about 5 minutes and doesn’t make your arms ache!! I tend to curl the ends in whilst gently rotating the brush up and down the hair, this works perfectly and sometimes I go over the hair twice to ensure it holds. I then spray with hairspray and voila! 
Even if you’re doing your hair and wearing your loungewear, you’ll feel so much better and who doesn’t want hair like Rachel Green eh? 
Here’s the link to the Big Hair Styler : https://www.babyliss.co.uk/big-hair-2885U.html 
Let me know if you re-create this yourself, I’d love to see pictures! And share by using the hashtag : #StayInWithBaByliss 
Ad #BaByliss #GetYourBaBylissLook

latestIgtvVideos.title: How To Make Frothy Coffee (kind of)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hello! Here is how to make the drink of lockdown (bar wine) frothy coffee. Probably a million better tutorials out there but there we go, and clearly I did not invent this haha but had a few messages asking if I’d make a video so hope you find this useful ☺️ and I hope you enjoy if you make it! . Patiently waiting for master chef to get in touch for me to be their new presenter 🤣🤣 enjoy!!
.

You will need :
1 TBSP instant coffee
1 TBSP sugar 
1 TBSP Hot water 
Whisk (electric or hand whisk)
Ice 
Milk of choice 
If you’re making for more people just do the quantities x people :) Any questions just ask!
